[normal]7.  THE CURRENT ROADMAP[bold]&#xa0;[bold]The interventions outlined in the roadmap provide an excellen
[normal]t pathway for the rapid deployment of a new system such as NET Power.  The challenge is to ensure that these provisions are implemented rapidly and available now in order to fund and launch development programmes.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]8.  INTERNATIONAL DEPLOYMENT OF CCS[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Rapi
[normal]d deployment and demonstration of
[normal] new cost effective CCS system
[normal]s by the UK will greatly influence worldwide
[normal] plans for deployment
[normal] 
[normal]and would position the UK at the centre of that development. The markets in China and India are vital for significantly impacti
[normal]ng total global CO
[normal]2
[normal] emissions targeting both new plants and retrofits.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]9.  CONSEQUENCIES[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Future levels of predicted world power demand are impossible to achieve without majority use of fossil fuels. If CCS is not widely adopted atmospheric CO2 levels will become unsustainable with grave risk of 
[normal]massive global disruption, co
[normal]nflicts and trauma. 
[normal] We have no
[normal] alternative to the successful deployment of CCS technology
